Comment.Text: The stimulation part of the scenario is similar to scenario 1-acquisition. If you keep the XML Stimulation Scenario Player box, you will be able to train the algorithms again on the recorded data.
You can browse each box' documentation by selecting the box and pressing F1
Finally, the Voting Classifier box choses which of the candidate column/ row has the P300

Overview This scenario can be used online once the spatial filter and the classifiers are trained. The XML Stimulation Scenario Player box still proposes some targets in order to eventually train the spatial filter / classifier again, but you may want to disconnect that box in order to have a real free time use of the speller. When you start this scenario, just press the "a" key to start the flash sequence. You will then be presented a blue letter that you have to focus on, followed by a 12 times flashing sequence of the whole grid. The detected letter will be presented in green. This will be repeated 10 times. If the performance of the system does not fit your requirements, just run 2-train-xDAWN and 3-train-classifier scenarios again on the data you just recorded. note: the recorded files go to the ${Path_Samples}/signals folder.

Each column / row has its own specific P300 detection pipeline which basically consists in : - a Stimulation Based Epoching box to select signal following the flash - a Classifier Processor to chose whether the selected signal is a target or not

The preprocessing of the signal is performed here... Note: be sure that the sampling rate and sample count per buffer you use in the acquisition server are compatible with the actual signal decimation factor
